#Text=Jones Phillips : Can you tell where you went to school at ?
#Text=I went through the Carmel school system .
#Text=And I ’m a graduate of Carmel High School — in 1988 .
#Text=And then I went on to college at Indiana University .
#Text=And ultimately received four degrees from Indiana University .
#Text=Tew :
#Text=And those degrees are in ... ?
#Text=I have a Bachelor of Arts degree in speech communications with minors in Spanish , biology , and an emphasis in chemistry .
#Text=I have a Masters in Public Affairs with an emphasis in international relations — or comparative international relations — and public finance .
#Text=I have a Masters of Science in Environmental Science , focused on applied ecology .
#Text=And then I have my law degree at the Indiana University School of Law at Indianapolis .
#Text=And lastly I want to know , how did you become interested in politics ?
#Text=I kind of backed my way into politics .
#Text=I had served as a page for Indiana State Senator Dan Burton .
#Text=And my mom and dad went to high school with Congressman Burton at Shortridge High School .
#Text=We had a family friendly connection there .
#Text=But I really did n't grow up in politics .
#Text=I did n't serve in student government — except one little stint when I was a graduate student at Indiana University .
#Text=I served one summer stint as a representative from the School of Public and Environmental Affairs .
#Text=But I really was n't involved in politics .
#Text=After I was getting ready to graduate from graduate school , I had planned to go to work for State Farm Insurance as a bond analyst .
#Text=About that time , I had made contact with Congressman Burton , who was going to become the first Republican chairman , to chair a Congressional committee in over 60[ ? ] years from Indiana .
#Text=And we got to talking and eventually that led to a job offer for me to come and join him on his personal and professional staff out in Washington D.C. working on Capitol Hill .
#Text=So I worked out of the personal office and then the professional staff of the House Committee on Government Reform , primarily focusing on Drug War policy .
#Text=I also did some work with the House International Relations Committee , which at the time was chaired by Congressman Ben Gillman from New York .
#Text=Hello Senator Delph , I ’m Sara Behnke .
#Text=We were wanting to know about your family and your work outside of the Indiana Senate .
#Text=My family is : My wife is Beth .
#Text=She is from Zionsville .
#Text=She grew up in Zionsville and graduated from Zionsville High School .
#Text=She is the daughter of Russ and Nancy Frankel and has one brother , who is younger , named Matthew .
#Text=My in-laws are now constituents of mine , which is nice because my mother-in-law could put my yard sign in her yard without confusing her neighbors .
